Module eigenproteins were calculated as the first principal component of the coexpressed genes in the module (
 Langfelder and Horvath, 2007; 
 Zhang and Horvath, 2005). The eigengene-based connectivity (kME) was used to represent the strength of a gene’s correlation with other gene module members. It is defined as the correlation between a gene’s expression and the module eigengene (
 Langfelder and Horvath, 2007; 
 Zhang and Horvath, 2005). Hub genes of a module were considered genes with high kME.
